            "name": "DataAgent_Foundry_Linda",
            "arguments": "{\"userQuestion\":\"Weather history in London, Ohio: list historical weather events, dates, event types, narratives, damages, injuries/deaths from the Weather table for location London, Ohio (or Madison County, OH)\"}",
            "output": "Here are historical weather events from the Weather table for London, Ohio (or Madison County, OH):\n\n1. Lake-Effect Snow\n   - Date: 1/24/2007 9:00 AM\n   - Narrative: Lake effect snow showers from the morning of the 24th into the afternoon of the 25th. Heaviest snow the morning of 25th, 6-10 inches across Lake County, max 12.5 inches in Madison Township.\n   - Property Damage: $100,000\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\n2. Winter Storm\n   - Date: 2/13/2007 4:00 AM\n   - Narrative: Snow began early 13th, increased during afternoon, 8-13 inches reported with gusty winds into 14th, finally tapered off that afternoon.\n   - Property Damage: $40,000\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\n3. Winter Storm\n   - Date: 2/13/2007 4:00 AM (separate report)\n   - Narrative: Snow and gusty winds from early 13th through 14th; 17.5 inches in Mentor, 9.4 inches south of Madison.\n   - Property Damage: $60,000\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\n4. Flood\n   - Date: 3/1/2007 11:30 PM\n   - Narrative: Several roads flooded and closed, some creeks rose out of banks across county.\n   - Property Damage: $3,000\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\n5. Flood\n   - Date: 3/14/2007 6:45 AM\n   - Narrative: Several roads flooded across the county.\n   - Property Damage: $3,000\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\n6. Winter Weather\n   - Date: 12/7/2007 12:00 AM\n   - Narrative: Two inches of snow measured at the county garage in London, 1.1 inches measured by spotter in Mount Sterling.\n   - Property Damage: $0\n   - Crop Damage: $0\n   - Injuries: 0\n   - Deaths: 0\n\nThese summaries include the event type, date, brief narrative, and reported property/crop damages, injuries, and deaths for notable weather events in the London/Madison County, Ohio area.\n",
            "status": "completed"
          },
